        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 7:24PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 724 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Mud Butte, or 42 miles northeast of Sturgis,
moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Butte
and north central Meade Counties, between Fairport and Mud Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
northwestern and west central South Dakota.</instruction>
